Executive Profile
Neil P. DeFeo  Independent Director, Hostess Brands, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships71$95,710
Background

		Mr. Neil P. DeFeo has been a Senior Advisor to CHARLESBANK Capital Partners since 2012. Mr. DeFeo has over 40 years of experience in the consumer products industry. He has been involved with over 50 different businesses and brands. Mr. DeFeo served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of The Sun Products Corporation until May 20, 2011, a private $1.5 billion company he helped to found in 2008. Mr. DeFeo served as President of Playtex Products, LLC at Edgewell ... Personal Care Company (formerly, Energizer Holdings Inc.) since October 4, 2004, Chief Executive Officer since October 4, 2004 until 2007 and Chairman of the Board since March 20, 2006. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Remington Products Co. LLC from January 1997 to September 2003 and also served as its Chairman since September 2001 until 2003. Prior to this, from 1993 to 1996, Mr. DeFeo served as Group Vice President, U.S. Operations of The Clorox Company, where he was responsible for its U.S. business. He also was responsible for corporate marketing, sales, manufacturing, engineering and logistics. Mr. DeFeo began his professional career with The Procter & Gamble Company with a position in manufacturing, followed by assignments in marketing and general management. For 25 years prior to 1993, Mr. DeFeo worked for Procter & Gamble in various executive positions, including as General Manager of New Products, Vice President and Managing Director, Worldwide Strategic Planning, Laundry and Cleaning Products. He has been Chairman of the board of directors of Peacock Foods since 2012. He served as the Chairman of The Sun Products Corporation from May 20, 2011 to January 25, 2012. He has been a Director of The Sun Products Corporation since May 20, 2011. He has been an Independent Director at Hostess Brands, Inc. (formerly, Gores Holdings, Inc.) since November 3, 2016. He serves as a Director of Cluett American Corp., (a textile manufacturer), Driscoll Strawberry Associates Inc., GoldToeMoretz, LLC, Cluett American Group and Cluett American Investment Corp., a Company in which Vestar or its affiliates has a significant equity interest. He serves as a Director of Driscoll's Strawberry Association Inc. Mr. DeFeo served as a Director of American Woodmark Corp. since July 15, 2003. He served as a Director of Playtex Products since October 4, 2004. He served as a Director of Spectrum Brands Holdings, Inc. (formerly, Rayovac Corp.) from September 30, 2003 until December 31, 2005. Mr. DeFeo served as a Director of Remington Products Co. LLC since January 1997. He served as a Director at Yale-New Haven Health Services Corporation. Over a 40+ year career, Mr. DeFeo has served on over 25 boards, both public and private, business and nonprofit. He serves on the board of directors of The Prostate Cancer Foundation. He contributes to a number of non-profit organizations including the United Way and March of Dimes. He served on the board of Directors for the National Association of Manufacturers. He served on Board of Trustees of Manhattan College from 2000 to June 2015 and Yale New Haven Hospital System from 2012 to February 2015. He is an active corporate advisor. Mr. DeFeo received a BS in Electrical Engineering from Manhattan College.Read Full Background




