Remington Products Announces Election of Neil P. DeFeo as Chairman




































Home » Remington Products Announces Election of Neil P. DeFeo as Chairman
Breaking News
Remington Products Announces Election of Neil P. DeFeo as Chairman


December 20, 2001



        Reprints
      






        No Comments
      



DeFoe is the company's president and CEO.    Remington Products Company,
L.L.C. announced that its Management Committee has elected Neil P. DeFeo,
President and Chief Executive Officer of the Company, to the additional post
of Chairman.
    Mr. DeFeo has served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Remington
since January of 1997.  Under his leadership, Remington has grown from net
sales of $241.6 million in 1997 to net sales of $365.1 million in 2000.
    From 1993 to 1996 Mr. DeFeo was Group Vice President -- US Operations for
The Clorox Company.  For 25 years prior to 1993, Mr. DeFeo worked for Procter
& Gamble in various executive positions including Vice President and Managing
Director, Worldwide Strategic Planning, Laundry and Cleaning Products.  Mr.
DeFeo is a Director of Cluett American Investment Corporation and Driscoll's
Strawberry Association, Inc. and serves as a Trustee of Manhattan College and
the National Association of Manufacturers.
    Remington Products Company, L.L.C., is a leading consumer products company
focusing on the development and marketing of personal care products.  The
Company designs and distributes electric shavers and accessories, grooming
products, hair care appliances, wellness products, and other small electric
consumer appliances.  The Company's headquarters are located at 60 Main
Street, Bridgeport, Connecticut.






